        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ui): improve accessible session history picker",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #95601.\n\nVoiceOver and keyboard users can open the Control UI chat session picker today, but the history entries still fall back to raw scoped session names when no explicit label exists, and the picker does not expose a direct rename action for each session. That leaves conversation history harder to identify, reopen, and manage without visual scanning.\n\nThis PR makes the chat session history picker expose human-readable titles, timestamps, active-state text, switch/reopen controls, and rename controls through standard keyboard-focusable buttons.\n\n## Summary\n\n- requests `includeDerivedTitles` for chat/recent-session loads so unlabeled conversations get readable derived titles instead of raw session keys\n- exposes each picker row as a keyboard-reachable switch action with a readable accessible name containing title, timestamp metadata, and active-state text\n- adds a keyboard-reachable rename action beside each picker row, reusing `sessions.patch` and preserving the chat-scoped refresh parameters\n- keeps the existing New Session control reachable with its existing `aria-label`\n- updates generated locale bundles after adding the new English picker action strings\n\n## Accessibility Notes\n\nThe picker now uses a regular list of session rows rather than an ARIA listbox. Each row contains separate, focusable controls for:\n\n- switching/reopening the session (`Switch to session: <title> · <timestamp> · Active` when current)\n- renaming the session (`Rename session: <title> · <timestamp> · Active` when current)\n\nThat avoids mixing an ARIA `option` with a sibling rename button while still preserving keyboard navigation through standard buttons and exposing the active session with `aria-current=\"page\"` plus the explicit `Active` text in the accessible name.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Added jsdom coverage that verifies derived titles render in the chat picker and the switch control accessible name includes title, timestamp metadata, and active-state text.\n- Added jsdom coverage that verifies each picker row exposes a rename control and persists the new label through `sessions.patch` while retaining chat-scoped refresh parameters.\n- Added controller coverage for forwarding `includeDerivedTitles` and for patch refresh override preservation.\n- Ran `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/sessions.test.ts`:\n  - `ui/src/ui/controllers/sessions.test.ts`: 81 passed\n  - `ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts`: 121 passed\n- Ran `corepack pnpm format:check ui/src/ui/chat/session-controls.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/sessions.ts ui/src/ui/session-display.ts ui/src/ui/types.ts ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/sessions.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-chat.ts ui/src/styles/chat/layout.css ui/src/i18n/locales/en.ts`: passed\n- Ran `git diff --check`: passed\n\n## Not Tested\n\n- I did not run a live macOS VoiceOver pass locally. The PR adds source-level and jsdom coverage for the expected accessible names, active state, derived-title display, rename action, and scoped session-list requests so the reporter can verify the branch with VoiceOver.\n",
